                       HILLS LIKE WHITE ELEPHANTS\
\
\
THE hills across the valley of the Ebro were long and white. On this\
side there was no shade and no trees and the station was between two\
lines of rails in the sun. Close against the side of the station there\
was the warm shadow of the building and a curtain, made of strings of\
bamboo beads, hung across the open door into the bar, to keep out flies.\
The American and the girl with him sat at a table in the shade, outside\
the building. It was very hot and the express from Barcelona would come\
in forty minutes. It stopped at this junction for two minutes and went\
on to Madrid.\
\
\'93What should we drink?\'94 the girl asked. She had taken off her hat and\
put it on the table.\
\
\'93It\'92s pretty hot,\'94 the man said.\
\
\'93Let\'92s drink beer.\'94\
\
\'93Dos cervezas,\'94 the man said into the curtain.\
\
\'93Big ones?\'94 a woman asked from the doorway.\
\
\'93Yes. Two big ones.\'94\
\
The woman brought two glasses of beer and two felt pads. She put the\
felt pads and the beer glasses on the table and looked at the man and\
the girl. The girl was looking off at the line of hills. They were white\
in the sun and the country was brown and dry.\
\
\'93They look like white elephants,\'94 she said.\
\
\'93I\'92ve never seen one,\'94 the man drank his beer.\
\
\'93No, you wouldn\'92t have.\'94\
\
\'93I might have,\'94 the man said. \'93Just because you say I wouldn\'92t have\
doesn\'92t prove anything.\'94\
\
The girl looked at the bead curtain. \'93They\'92ve painted something on it,\'94\
she said. \'93What does it say?\'94\
\
\'93Anis del Toro. It\'92s a drink.\'94\
\
\'93Could we try it?\'94\
\
The man called \'93Listen\'94 through the curtain. The woman came out from the\
bar.\
\
\'93Four reales.\'94\
\
\'93We want two Anis del Toro.\'94\
\
\'93With water?\'94\
\
\'93Do you want it with water?\'94\
\
\'93I don\'92t know,\'94 the girl said. \'93Is it good with water?\'94\
\
\'93It\'92s all right.\'94\
\
\'93You want them with water?\'94 asked the woman.\
\
\'93Yes, with water.\'94\
\
\'93It tastes like licorice,\'94 the girl said and put the glass down.\
\
\'93That\'92s the way with everything.\'94\
\
\'93Yes,\'94 said the girl. \'93Everything tastes of licorice. Especially all the\
things you\'92ve waited so long for, like absinthe.\'94\
\
\'93Oh, cut it out.\'94\
\
\'93You started it,\'94 the girl said. \'93I was being amused. I was having a\
fine time.\'94\
\
\'93Well, let\'92s try and have a fine time.\'94\
\
\'93All right. I was trying. I said the mountains looked like white\
elephants. Wasn\'92t that bright?\'94\
\
\'93That was bright.\'94\
\
\'93I wanted to try this new drink. That\'92s all we do, isn\'92t it\'97look at\
things and try new drinks?\'94\
\
\'93I guess so.\'94\
\
The girl looked across at the hills.\
\
\'93They\'92re lovely hills,\'94 she said. \'93They don\'92t really look like white\
elephants. I just meant the coloring of their skin through the trees.\'94\
\
\'93Should we have another drink?\'94\
\
\'93All right.\'94\
\
The warm wind blew the bead curtain against the table.\
\
\'93The beer\'92s nice and cool,\'94 the man said.\
\
\'93It\'92s lovely,\'94 the girl said.\
\
\'93It\'92s really an awfully simple operation, Jig,\'94 the man said. \'93It\'92s not\
really an operation at all.\'94\
\
The girl looked at the ground the table legs rested on.\
\
\'93I know you wouldn\'92t mind it, Jig. It\'92s really not anything. It\'92s just\
to let the air in.\'94\
\
The girl did not say anything.\
\
\'93I\'92ll go with you and I\'92ll stay with you all the time. They just let the\
air in and then it\'92s all perfectly natural.\'94\
\
\'93Then what will we do afterward?\'94\
\
\'93We\'92ll be fine afterward. Just like we were before.\'94\
\
\'93What makes you think so?\'94\
\
\'93That\'92s the only thing that bothers us. It\'92s the only thing that\'92s made\
us unhappy.\'94\
\
The girl looked at the bead curtain, put her hand out and took hold of\
two of the strings of beads.\
\
\'93And you think then we\'92ll be all right and be happy.\'94\
\
\'93I know we will. You don\'92t have to be afraid. I\'92ve known lots of people\
that have done it.\'94\
\
\'93So have I,\'94 said the girl. \'93And afterward they were all so happy.\'94\
\
\'93Well,\'94 the man said, \'93if you don\'92t want to you don\'92t have to. I\
wouldn\'92t have you do it if you didn\'92t want to. But I know it\'92s perfectly\
simple.\'94\
\
\'93And you really want to?\'94\
\
\'93I think it\'92s the best thing to do. But I don\'92t want you to do it if you\
don\'92t really want to.\'94\
\
\'93And if I do it you\'92ll be happy and things will be like they were and\
you\'92ll love me?\'94\
\
\'93I love you now. You know I love you.\'94\
\
\'93I know. But if I do it, then it will be nice again if I say things are\
