\
\'93What did you say?\'94\
\
\'93I said we could have everything.\'94\
\
\'93We can have everything.\'94\
\
\'93No, we can\'92t.\'94\
\
\'93We can have the whole world.\'94\
\
\'93No, we can\'92t.\'94\
\
\'93We can go everywhere.\'94\
\
\'93No, we can\'92t. It isn\'92t ours any more.\'94\
\
\'93It\'92s ours.\'94\
\
\'93No, it isn\'92t. And once they take it away, you never get it back.\'94\
\
\'93But they haven\'92t taken it away.\'94\
\
\'93We\'92ll wait and see.\'94\
\
\'93Come on back in the shade,\'94 he said. \'93You mustn\'92t feel that way.\'94\
\
\'93I don\'92t feel any way,\'94 the girl said. \'93I just know things.\'94\
\
\'93I don\'92t want you to do anything that you don\'92t want to do\'97\'97\'94\
\
\'93Nor that isn\'92t good for me,\'94 she said. \'93I know. Could we have another\
beer?\'94\
\
\'93All right. But you\'92ve got to realize\'97\'97\'94\
\
\'93I realize,\'94 the girl said. \'93Can\'92t we maybe stop talking?\'94\
